# Walkthrough: Container & Steam Integration

## Changes Made

### 1. Game Settings UI — Container Selector
**File:** [ContainerDetailFragment.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/ContainerDetailFragment.java)

- [loadWineVersionSpinner](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/ContainerDetailFragment.java#1081-1151): When in shortcut mode ([isShortcutMode()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/ContainerDetailFragment.java#303-306) or `createShortcutForAppId > 0`), the "Wine Version" dropdown now **only lists existing containers** (prefixed with `"Container: "`), instead of raw Wine/Proton packages.
- When editing an existing shortcut, the spinner auto-selects the container currently bound to that shortcut (via stored `container_id` extra).
- **Save logic**: When saving, the selected container name is parsed, the matching [Container](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/container/Container.java#24-640) object is found, and `shortcut.putExtra("container_id", ...)` is updated. This allows switching games between containers at any time.

### 2. x86_64 Boot Hang Fix
**File:** [GuestProgramLauncherComponent.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/xenvironment/components/GuestProgramLauncherComponent.java)

**Root cause:** The `HODLL` environment variable (`wowbox64.dll` / `libwow64fex.dll`) was being set for **all** container types, including standard [x86_64](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/Reference/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/xenvironment/components/GuestProgramLauncherComponent.java#347-373). This variable tells Wine to use WoW64 translation DLLs, which only exist in Arm64EC Wine packages. Setting it for x86_64 caused Wine to hang during initialization.

**Fix:** `HODLL` is now only set when `wineInfo.isArm64EC()` is true. x86_64 containers use Box64 binary translation directly without WoW64 DLLs.

```diff
 else {
-    if (emulator.toLowerCase().equals("fexcore"))
-        envVars.put("HODLL", "libwow64fex.dll");
-    else
-        envVars.put("HODLL", "wowbox64.dll");
-
     if (wineInfo.isArm64EC()) {
+        if (emulator.toLowerCase().equals("fexcore"))
+            envVars.put("HODLL", "libwow64fex.dll");
+        else
+            envVars.put("HODLL", "wowbox64.dll");
         command = winePath + "/" + guestExecutable;
     }
     else {
+        // x86_64 uses Box64 directly, no HODLL
         command = imageFs.getBinDir() + "/box64 " + guestExecutable;
     }
 }
```

